main event: An object bright as a first magnitude star was observed in flight on 20 June 1963.
interesting points: The object was at 17 degrees elevation on a course of 340 degrees true., The sighting was believed to be a satellite., Flight to the horizon with no reported maneuvers., There was insufficient data due to conflicting information., The duration of the sighting was not reported.
sighted object: an object bright as a first magnitude star
